---

Step 8: Viva Questions

1. What is Selection Sort?

Sorting algorithm that repeatedly selects the smallest element and puts it in correct position.



2. Time Complexity?

Best, Worst, Average → O(n²)



3. Space Complexity?

O(1) → in-place sorting



4. Why do we use pass?

Each pass places one element in its correct position



5. Difference between Selection Sort and Bubble Sort?

Selection Sort → selects min element and swaps once per pass

Bubble Sort → swaps adjacent elements repeatedly



6. Why count comparisons?

To analyze efficiency of the algorithm



7. How do you print top scores?

Sort array → print from largest element (S[n-1])



8. Can this program handle <5 students?

Yes, loop condition i >= 0 ensures no error




